OL,3,CParents urged to protect babies from
OL,4,Cwhooping cough
OL,6,FLauren Hall reports on the rising
OL,7,Flevels of whooping cough which can be
OL,8,Fparticularly harmful to young babies
OL,10,FParents are being urged to get their
OL,11,Fbabies vaccinated against whooping
OL,12,Fcough following a sharp rise in cases
OL,13,Facross the UK.
OL,15,FThe bacterial infection, clinically
OL,16,Fknown as pertussis, affects the lungs.
OL,17,FIt can be caught by anyone but it is
OL,18,Fparticularly harmful to infants, which
OL,19,Fis why vaccines are offered during
OL,20,Fpregnancy and after the babies are
OL,21,Fborn at 8, 12 and 16 weeks old.
