OL,4,Cwhooping cough
OL,6,FThe first signs of infection are
OL,7,Fsimilar to a cold, such as a runny
OL,8,Fnose and sore throat.
OL,10,FAfter about a week, the infection can
OL,11,Fdevelop into coughing bouts that last
OL,12,Ffor a few minutes and are typically
OL,13,Fworse at night. Some may also make a
OL,14,Fdistinctive "whoop" - gasps for
OL,15,Fbreath, in between bouts of coughing.
OL,17,FIt can affect young babies' breathing
OL,18,Fand lead to serious complications
OL,19,Fincluding seizures or pneumonia. It
OL,20,Fcan also be fatal.
