OL,6,FSteve Russell, National Director for
OL,7,FVaccinations and Screening at NHS
OL,8,FEngland, said: "With whooping cough on
OL,9,Fthe rise, it is important that
OL,10,Ffamilies come forward to get the
OL,11,Fprotection they need. If you are
OL,12,Fpregnant and have not been vaccinated
OL,13,Fyet, or your child is not up-to-date
OL,14,Fwith whooping cough or other routine
OL,15,Fvaccinations, please contact your GP
OL,16,Fas soon as possible, and if you or
OL,17,Fyour child have symptoms ask for an
OL,18,Furgent GP appointment or get help from
OL,19,FNHS 111."
